    "We then introduce how fine-grained rewards are computed and used to train the LM with RL or RS in § 2.2.",
    "Finally, we describe how to train the LM with holistic rewards for comparison purposes in § 2.3. et al. (2023b) observe that the performance of open-sourced LMs like LLaMA-2 for attributable generation is far from satisfactory.",
    "In particular, we notice that even with in-context learning, a base LLaMA-2-7B can only generate citations for a very small portion of sentences in its responses.",
    "As previous studies (Touvron et al., 2023; Wu et al., 2023) often perform RS or RL training on top of a reasonably good initial LM as a starting point, we first learn a better LM capable of generating in-text citations by distilling knowledge from a powerful proprietary model such as ChatGPTfoot_0.",
    "For each question in the training set, we prompt Chat-GPT with in-context demonstrations (Brown et al., 2020) to generate answers that contain citations (See Appendix I)."
